{"questionId":"9073478","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The diagram represents an ideal, monatomic gas that first undergoes a compression, then an increase in pressure.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4327dedf256a6ffef6c48423c35b4ce333dac97b.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An adiabatic process then increases the volume of the gas to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mrow></msup><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Outline how an approximate adiabatic change can be achieved.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">adiabatic means no transfer of heat in or out of the system </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">✓</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">should be fast </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">✓</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">«can be slow if» the system is insulated </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">✓</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">OWTTE</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073478","referenceCode":"20N.3.SL.TZ0.b(ii)","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Outline how an approximate adiabatic change can be achieved.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}